post_text:
We're pleased to offer our 8th Annual Girls in Engineering and Technology Camp at NVOT for 5th-8th graders. Thanks in part to the camp, we are seeing our female enrollment in Technology and Engineering courses at the high school at well over 30% average, which is outstanding considering just a few years ago we were at 10%!

If you would please help us in sharing this information, we'd greatly appreciate it!

Dates: Tuesday, June 25th through Friday, June 28th 2019 (4 days)
Times: 9 am to 2 pm daily
Location: Northern Valley Regional High School at Old Tappan
Cost: $125 per student
Contact: Alex Paspalas, paspalasa@nvnet.org

Please join us February 13th for our Third Annual Family STEM Night!
All 7th and 8th graders in Northern Valley are invited WITH a participating adult to participate in a fun and engaging hands-on wearable tech activity using lights and conductive thread. The same take-home materials can be used to prototype health monitoring devices and high tech fashion like clothing and sneakers. Approximately 20 students from each district will be accepted. Unfortunately, younger siblings cannot be accommodated.

Where: NVRHS at Old Tappan Cafeteria, 140 Central Ave.
When: February 13, 2019 6 PM - 8 PM

RSVP: By 2/8/19 using the Google Form: https://goo.gl/forms/M8EWNn8xliqV8xSE2
For planning purposes, all participants must register and will receive an email confirmation.

Any questions? Contact Ms. Jennifer Cusmano, Mr. Dave Janosz or Ms. April Vella
(cusmano@nvnet.org, janosz@nvnet.org, vella@nvnet.org)

post_text:
Northern Valley Regional High School District is one of two districts in Bergen County and 447 school districts in the U.S. and Canada being honored by the College Board with placement on the 8th Annual AP 庐 District Honor Roll. To be included on the 8th Annual Honor Roll, Northern Valley had to, since 2015, increase the number of students participating in Advanced Placement (AP) while also increasing or maintaining the percentage of students earning AP Exam scores of 3 or higher. Reaching these goals shows that this district is successfully identifying motivated, academically prepared students who are ready for AP courses.

Read more at:
https://apcentral.collegeboard.org/score-reports-data/awards/honor-roll

Now open to all 7th and 8th graders in Northern Valley sending towns!

Family STEM Night at Northern Valley Regional HS

Its Your Night to be a Biomedical Engineer!

Design an Artificial Heart Valve

Please Join Us!!!!

Why: STEM is fun for the whole family!
What: Participate in a fun and engaging hands-on biomedical engineering activity
Who: All 7th AND 8th graders in Northern Valley WITH a participating adult
Approximately 20 students from each district will be accepted.
Unfortunately, younger siblings cannot be accommodated.
Where: NVRHS at Demarest Cafeteria, 150 Knickerbocker Rd.
When: January 11, 2017 6 PM - 8 PM (Snow Date: 1/18/17)

RSVP: By 1/8/17 using the Google Form: http://tinyurl.com/zbomrje
For planning purposes, all participants must register and will receive an email confirmation.

Any questions? Contact Ms. Jennifer Cusmano, Mr. Dave Janosz or Ms. April Vella
(cusmano@nvnet.org, janosz@nvnet.org, vella@nvnet.org)

Extra, extra! The new north edition of Northern Valley Press just hit the printing press!

On the front cover this week: The Borough of Old Tappan has a new mayor for the first time since 2000, as John Kramer takes over for Victor Polce. Plus there's a new man in charge of the Bergen County Prosecutor's Office, and the Northern Valley Regional High School District Board of Education fields ideas from the public about how to promote an upcoming referendum that seeks to make upgrades at various school facilities.

All those stories and many more from your community in this edition. Don't miss it!

7-8PM Help the clubs with concession stands
7-8PM Greet and help find seating for guests
8-10PM Help the clubs with concession stands

Shari Moss & Soci Kayserian

post_text:
Before a standing room only audience at the recent Northern Valley Board of Education meeting, President Alice Comer presented service plaques to Lenny Albanese (Closter 37 years) and Ron Schwartzman (Demarest 4 years) recognizing their dedication and commitment to the students, parents, staff, and community.

Ron Schwartzman previously served as a member of the K-8 Demarest BOE, Library Board dedicating over 20 years of volunteer service to the Northern Valley Region.

Lenny Albanese is a beloved legend in Northern Valley, well known for his passionate love of the students along with his expertise in facilities and finance. When you consider the New Jersey School Board Association recently celebrated the 100th anniversary of the organization, Lennys 37 years of service to the NVRHS Board is truly remarkable.

The Northern Valley Board will seat two new members Tiffany Kaplan and Joseph Argenziano, and elect new officers at their re-organization meeting on January 5, 2015.

post_text: Northern Valley-Demarest Regional High School was awarded the Big North All-Sport Banner for accumulating the most points during the Fall, Winter, and Spring Athletic Seasons. The school won seven Big North Divisional Championships during the 2013-14 season. The school was also recognized for outstanding sportsmanship by the NJSIAA, and will be receiving the NJ State Interscholastic Athletic Association Sportsmanship Banner. NV-Demarest Athletic Director, Greg Butler stated These accomplishments reflect the hard work and dedication of our student-athletes and coaching staff. The success of our Boys and Girls teams along with demonstrating good sportsmanship is something we are all proud of at NV-Demarest. Winning with classit does get better then that!

post_text:
Regarding this afternoon's suspicious device incident:
The Demarest Police Chief has shared that this is an ongoing criminal investigation. Anyone with information about this incident is encouraged to call the Demarest Police or anonymously report to WeTip at 1-800-78-Crime. Parents, please make sure you discuss this incident with your child and, if needed, seek the appropriate counseling. Counselors will be available on Monday if students need assistance.

post_text:
Suspicious Device Being Investigated at NV Demarest

On Friday, February 7 at approximately 1:15 p.m. a suspicious item was found in one of the gymnasiums in the building. All students and staff have safely been evacuated to school grounds outside. The police were called and precautions have been taken including bringing in the bomb squad to investigate. An inside area of the school building is being secured so that students may be able to return indoors while the area where the item was found is being cleared. There is no need to come to the school as precautionary measures have been taken and all students and staff are safe. Updates will be posted as information continues to become available.
